    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob//cmake.deps/deps.txt specifies URLs for downloading tarballs of bundled dependencies, along with their SHA256s.\r\nSome of them point to auto-generated tarballs from GitHub, like https://github.com/libuv/libuv/archive/v1.48.0.tar.gz, but these are known to not be stable and have already changed in the past.\r\n\r\nGitHub claim to not change them too frequently in the future, but there is no guarantee: https://github.blog/2023-02-21-update-on-the-future-stability-of-source-code-archives-and-hashes/\r\nUnfortunately, not all of the necessary projects ship non-autogenerated tarballs. One way to work around this is to mirror the files oneself somewhere.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nBuild should not break unexpectedly because GitHub changed their tarball generation strategy in the future.",
